text.tspan: Death rates from all causes in France over the 20th century
The reported annual death rate per 100,000 people in each demographic, based on vital statistics. This is shown
as a crude rate per 100,000 people; it does not account for changes in the age structure of the population.
Data source: Institut National d'Études Démographiques
